# AWS CDK Conventions

## Free-Tier Defaults
- EC2: `t2.micro` (750 hrs/month free for 12 months)
- RDS: `db.t3.micro` Postgres, single-AZ, no Multi-AZ
- ElastiCache: `cache.t3.micro` Redis, single node
- Always set `removalPolicy: RemovalPolicy.DESTROY` for non-production resources

## Stack Patterns
```typescript
// Always tag all resources
Tags.of(this).add('Project', 'my-stack-app');
Tags.of(this).add('Environment', props.env ?? 'dev');
```

## Resource Naming
- Use `id` prefixes matching the stack name: `MyStackAppVpc`, `MyStackAppDb`
- Use `this.stackName` for dynamic naming to avoid hardcoded names

## Security
- Never hardcode secrets — use `aws-cdk-lib/aws-secretsmanager` or SSM Parameter Store
- Security groups: allow only required ports (8000 for app, 5432 for RDS internal only)
- RDS must NOT be publicly accessible: `publiclyAccessible: false`

## Deployment
```bash
cd infrastructure
npm run cdk deploy        # deploy stack
npm run cdk diff          # preview changes
npm run cdk destroy       # tear down (saves cost)
```
